# K-means Clustering Analysis
def run_kmeans_segmentation(df, clustering_features):
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(df[clustering_features])

    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    df['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(X_scaled)
    centers = pd.DataFrame(kmeans.cluster_centers_, columns=clustering_features)

    print("\\n Cluster Centers:\\n", pd.DataFrame(scaler.inverse_transform(kmeans.cluster_centers_), columns=clustering_features))

    # Heuristic labeling
    cluster_labels = {}
    for i in range(4):
        center = centers.loc[i]
        if center['TotalSpend(USD)'] > centers['TotalSpend(USD)'].mean() and center['OnTimeDeliveryRate(%)'] > centers['OnTimeDeliveryRate(%)'].mean():
            label = 'Strategic Partners'
        elif center['TotalSpend(USD)'] > centers['TotalSpend(USD)'].mean():
            label = 'High-Cost Specialists'
        elif center['DefectRate(%)'] > centers['DefectRate(%)'].mean():
            label = 'High-Risk Liabilities'
        else:
            label = 'Operational Workhorses'
        cluster_labels[i] = label

    df['Supplier_Segment_KMeans'] = df['Cluster'].map(cluster_labels)

    print("\\n Supplier Segments (Top 5):")
    print(df[['SupplierID', 'Name', 'Cluster', 'Supplier_Segment_KMeans']].head())
    print("\\n Supplier Count by Segment:")
    print(df['Supplier_Segment_KMeans'].value_counts())

# ---------------- #
# Feature Settings #
# ---------------- #
clustering_features = [
    'TotalSpend(USD)', 'OnTimeDeliveryRate(%)', 'DefectRate(%)', 'ESGScore(%)'
]

run_kmeans_segmentation(df, clustering_features)
